{"id":"335942792_Computation_of_Admissible_Marking_Sets_in_Weighted_Synchronization-Free_Petri_Nets_by_Dynamic_Programming","abstract":"We study the computation of admissible marking sets in generalized Petri nets. We first show that the admissibility checking in generalized Petri net is NP-hard. Then we consider a special subclass of generalized Petri nets called \n$weighted-synchronization-free\\ nets$ \nin which each transition has at most one input place. For a net in this subclass, we propose a generating function to compute by dynamic programming the set of admissible markings for a given \n$generalize\\ mutual\\ exclusion\\ constraint$ \n.","authors":["Ziyue Ma","Guanghui Zhu","Zhiwu Li","Alessandro Giua"],"meta":["September 2019IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control PP(99):1-1","DOI:10.1109/TAC.2019.2942570"],"references":["281845323_Design_of_Optimal_Petri_Net_Controllers_for_Disjunctive_Generalized_Mutual_Exclusion_Constraints","271901964_Fault_Model_Identification_and_Synthesis_in_Petri_Nets","260662453_Petri_net_supervisor_for_DES_with_uncontrollable_and_unobservable_transition","254060972_Deadlock_Control_of_Automated_Manufacturing_Systems_Based_on_Petri_Nets-A_Literature_Review","239482725_Control_of_discrete_event_system","226969002_A_Survey_of_Petri_Net_Methods_for_Controlled_Discrete_Event_Systems","224662214_Generalized_mutual_exclusion_contraints_on_nets_with_uncontrollable_transitions","220652116_Supervision_Based_on_Place_Invariants_A_Survey","322671081_Computation_of_admissible_marking_sets_in_weighted_state_machines_by_dynamic_programming","318811231_Robust_Deadlock_Avoidance_for_Sequential_Resource_Allocation_Systems_With_Resource_Outages","308877339_Petri_net_controllers_for_Generalized_Mutual_Exclusion_Constraints_with_floor_operators","304662712_Petri-Net_Controller_Synthesis_for_Partially_Controllable_and_Observable_Discrete_Event_Systems","304573561_Characterization_of_Admissible_Marking_Sets_in_Petri_Nets_With_Conflicts_and_Synchronizat